ng the `TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments` MSBuild property in the csproj to pass `--hotreload` by default, since that's the idiomatic way to configure the new Microsoft Testing Platform. This way the `--hotreload` flag gets automatically passed whenever running `dotnet test`, so hot reload stays enabled without needing environment variables.","outputTokens":1224,"requestId":"3019:527BE:48F8134:4FB95C8:6A031070"},"id":"3b68633c-bcf4-4286-92e8-49b3c68f9fcc","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:35:36.082Z","parentId":"a0053c0c-5890-4104-914b-9e3c8256b637"}
